  "description": [
    "PRITAIN BARS WHILE LONE WOODHO USE SEES PERIL IN FOREIGN HOLDINGS ON CALIFORNIA LAND Expert Would Have Coming Conference on Ars Reductions Informed That Washington Will Restrict Foreign Operations Among 011 Re serves of Pacific Coast and Will Demand That England and Holland Lift the Ban Now in Force Against Developments by Outside Capital This is the fourth of a series of articles revealing the in bide facts regarding the factors that dominate the whole dis armament question written especially for The Washington Times by Henry Woodhouse He is a foremost authority and leader of the National Defense movement in which he took the initiative in 1912 when he started to organize aero squadrons for New York National Guard and for different States For seven years Mr Woodhouse whose reports on national defense matters have been published as Congressional docu nents since 1918 has studied and followed the development of the international oil question During the war he was requested to make a report for the President and the War Department and he made an exhaustive study of the worlds oil production and oil resources and has followed closely the inside developments of the oil situation and other dom inant"
